00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:33,735
Good, great. Send it.

301
00:16:33,802 --> 00:16:37,605
The Company's e-Mailing
Tia's credit card history.

302
00:16:37,725 --> 00:16:40,919
You know, I'm thinking more and
more that this is an inside job.

303
00:16:41,039 --> 00:16:44,559
Why?
A couple reasons.

304
00:16:44,679 --> 00:16:46,144
The hardware he
brought to the meet.

305
00:16:46,264 --> 00:16:48,008
He could read Scylla
right on the spot.

306
00:16:48,128 --> 00:16:49,297
Since he's disappeared,

307
00:16:49,417 --> 00:16:51,961
I should be able to find
this man, and I can't.

308
00:16:52,081 --> 00:16:54,422
People you can't find are
usually Company.

309
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:55,679
How does that change anything?

310
00:16:55,799 --> 00:16:56,411
It doesn't.

311
00:16:56,531 --> 00:16:58,292
It just makes everything harder.

312
00:17:02,837 --> 00:17:04,632
Lincoln...

313
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:05,973
Yeah?

314
00:17:06,093 --> 00:17:08,936
When are we going to get this
out of the way?

315
00:17:09,004 --> 00:17:10,048
What?

316
00:17:10,168 --> 00:17:11,790
Of all the mercenary humps
I've thrown at guys

317
00:17:11,910 --> 00:17:15,447
In my lifetime, I think I'm due
for one I want.

318
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:16,980
Don't flatter yourself.

319
00:17:20,202 --> 00:17:21,804
Too late.

320
00:17:23,546 --> 00:17:26,020
Name it.

321
00:17:26,088 --> 00:17:28,256
And I do mean anything.

322
00:17:31,624 --> 00:17:33,861
A big ol' fat load
of nothin'!

323
00:17:33,929 --> 00:17:37,042
A big ol' goose egg.

324
00:17:37,162 --> 00:17:40,612
SELF:
Nothing. Old address
books, photographs,

