00:24:23,517 --> 00:24:24,851
Okay, okay, okay.

466
00:24:24,918 --> 00:24:27,487
Where is it?
Where's Scylla?

467
00:24:27,554 --> 00:24:29,255
What have you
got in here?

468
00:24:29,323 --> 00:24:31,991
Huh?

469
00:24:32,059 --> 00:24:34,460
Three joints.

470
00:24:41,835 --> 00:24:43,336
I'm on probation.

471
00:24:43,404 --> 00:24:45,471
Is this going to send me back?

472
00:24:51,345 --> 00:24:53,079
Make yourself
a helmet, pal.

473
00:24:53,147 --> 00:24:56,049
Just like old times.

474
00:24:59,887 --> 00:25:01,254
Bring her back.

475
00:25:01,322 --> 00:25:03,222
You know
I can't do that.

476
00:25:03,290 --> 00:25:05,992
But, look, there's
some stuff

477
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:07,660
<i>That I can do.</i>

478
00:25:07,728 --> 00:25:08,828
It's not going to be the same,

479
00:25:08,896 --> 00:25:11,197
But we're going
to figure it out.

480
00:25:11,265 --> 00:25:12,732
And, no matter what,

481
00:25:12,800 --> 00:25:15,437
It's still going
to be me and you.

482
00:25:16,504 --> 00:25:19,505
I am thrilled that
You're enjoying your trip to the mountains,

483
00:25:19,573 --> 00:25:22,008
But it's not
an open-Ended vacation.

484
00:25:22,076 --> 00:25:25,612
